vim installation and environment setup instructions
Author : Ramkumar N
Date : 1-June-2017

Prerequsites:
1) cmake
		On Ubuntu:
			1) sudo apt-get install cmake
		On Arch:	
			1) sudo pacman -S cmake

2) git
		on Ubuntu:
			1) sudo apt-get install git
		On Arch:
			1) sudo pacman -S git

3) clang
		On Arch:
			1) sudo pacman -S clang
		Others:
			1) goto 'http://releases.llvm.org/download.html' and download the apt version of clang for your distro.  			
			2) sudo tar -C /usr/local -xvf clang*.tar.xz

4) python-dev
		On Ubuntu:
			1) sudo apt-get isntall python3-dev
		On Arch: python3-dev is not required.

Installation Instructions:
1) git clone https://github.com/ramkalath/config_files
2) cd config_files/vim/
3) sudo source ./install.sh

4) manually start vim and type <Esc> :PluginInstall and wait
Enjoy!!!
